speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for War (1) why foreign


women married in ex-enemy territories to British soldiers are classified as B category wives, and are denied certain perquisites such as access to N.A.A.F.I. stores, etc.;

(2) why British wives of serving soldiers who reach their husbands in certain ex-enemy territories on their own and not his Department's initiative are treated on arrival as B category wives by the military authorities.
